# OxPlayer Relay Server Configuration

# Server Configuration
LISTEN_ADDR=:8080
LOG_DIR=/data/logs

# Firebase Cloud Messaging (FCM) Configuration
# FCM is optional - the cast system works without it using long polling
# To enable FCM push notifications, set one of the following:

# Option 1: Standard Google Cloud credentials path
# GOOGLE_APPLICATION_CREDENTIALS=/path/to/firebase-serviceAccountKey.json

# Option 2: Custom FCM credentials path
# FCM_CREDENTIALS_PATH=/path/to/firebase-serviceAccountKey.json

# How to obtain Firebase credentials:
# 1. Go to https://console.firebase.google.com/
# 2. Select your project
# 3. Go to Project Settings > Service Accounts
# 4. Click "Generate New Private Key"
# 5. Save the JSON file securely (DO NOT commit to version control)
# 6. Set the path above

# Security Notes:
# - Never commit the credentials JSON file to version control
# - Add firebase-serviceAccountKey.json to .gitignore
# - Use restrictive file permissions (chmod 600)
# - Rotate credentials regularly (every 90 days)

# Without FCM:
# - Cast jobs are delivered via long polling (30-second intervals)
# - Average latency: ~15 seconds
# - No additional configuration needed

# With FCM:
# - Cast jobs are delivered instantly via push notifications
# - Average latency: <1 second
# - Requires Firebase project setup
